<h2 id="7--neovim">7. <a href="/assets/img/editors/neovim-logo.png"><img src="/assets/img/editors/neovim-logo.png" alt="NeoVim" /></a> Neovim</h2>
<p><img src="/assets/img/editors/neovim-min.png" alt="NeoVim" /></p>

<p>Neovim is an improved Vim fork, especially in the organization of plugins. In our Vim course there is also a lot of Neovim content.</p>

<p>Official Website: <a href="https://neovim.io/">https://neovim.io/</a></p>

<p>To install it use the package manager of your distribution, examples:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">sudo </span>emerge <span class="nt">-a</span> neovim <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo, ..</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>neovim <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Mint, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> neovim <span class="c"># Arch, Manjaro,...</span></code></pre></figure>

